{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"0782f66a529ccd24e18226f5eebab20a90bea166"},"timestamp":1291886800,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyODQ4NjQx","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/434","origin":"github"},"title":"don't cache .parrot_current_git_describe","message":"When configuring parrot, the value for \"git-describe\" is taken from the cache file if it is present.\n\nHere's a not-uncommon workflow that breaks in this case:\n- realclean \n- build\n- git pull\n- configure # XXX This does not update the sha1-describe.\n- build\n\nUnless there's a super compelling reason to cache this file, the value shouldn't even be stored on disk - it should go into the config hash and be calculated every time you run configure.\n\n(similar arguments may cover other newly generated .parrot files.)\n\nOriginally http://trac.parrot.org/parrot/ticket/1884","files":null}]}